nce a takeover of Anacott Steel at $15 per share;=C2=A0you should buy some.=
=E2=80=9D I go back to my office, open up my brokerage app, and am about to=
 buy 10,000 short-dated out-of-the-money call options when I think: =E2=80=
=9CWait, no, this is insider trading, I will get in trouble for this.=E2=80=
=9D I close the app.</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Instead, I pick up my=
 phone and call you. =E2=80=9CHey,=E2=80=9D I say, =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99ll be=
t you a million dollars that Anacott Steel closes above $13 this Friday.=E2=
=80=9D You are a degenerate gambler and have never heard of the concept of =
adverse selection, so you say =E2=80=9Cha, Anacott Steel is at $10 now, thi=
s is easy money, it=E2=80=99s a bet.=E2=80=9D The next day, the takeover of=
fer is announced, the stock goes to $14, and I collect $1 million from you.=
=C2=A0</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Did I commit insider trading=3F Oh =
man is this not legal advice, but my gut is: yes=3F Technically I didn=E2=
=80=99t trade any stock =E2=80=94=C2=A0I just made a bet with you =E2=80=94=
 but I=E2=80=99m not sure that matters. Our bet is, arguably, a =E2=80=9Cse=
curity-based swap=E2=80=9D: We have agreed to exchange payments based on th=
e future value of a security (the Anacott Steel stock).<a href=3D"#footnote=
