d-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;"> <span>[3]</span> =
</a> You wouldn=E2=80=99t necessarily do that if you were a degenerate gamb=
ler, but realistically if I am calling someone to bet on the future=C2=A0pr=
ice of a stock, I=E2=80=99m probably calling a=C2=A0<em>bank </em>or other =
trading firm, and the bank will probably hedge. Therefore, while my bet is =
not an=C2=A0<em>actual=C2=A0</em>insider trade in Anacott Steel stock, it p=
redictably=C2=A0<em>causes</em> trades in Anacott Steel stock. It=E2=80=99s=
 not just between us; somebody else =E2=80=94=C2=A0some seller of the stock=
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0is indirectly on the wrong side of my inside information.</=
